## How to work in this repo

1. **Read first, edit second.** Before any non-trivial change, read `PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, and the relevant section of `TASKS.md`.
2. **Work in vertical slices.** A "feature" is end-to-end: schema → API → worker → UI → test → docs. Do not stub out one layer and call it done.
3. **Tests are mandatory.** No new code without tests.
4. **{{DOMAIN_SPECIFIC_RULE_IF_ANY}}** — e.g., for AI products: "Citations are mandatory; outputs without citations are invalid." For regulated products: "Use 'aligned with X' not 'certified by X'." For multi-tenant: "Every table has tenant_id."
5. **Phase gates are real.** Each phase ends with a `product-owner-reviewer` check via `/phase-review`. Do not start the next phase until the previous one has been signed off.

## Subagents

Use the right subagent for the job. Defined in `.claude/agents/`:

- `product-manager` — scoping, user stories, acceptance criteria
- `solution-architect` — system design, ADRs, trade-offs
- `security-architect` — threat modeling, authz, secrets, audit log
- `backend-engineer` — backend code, schemas, migrations, workers
- `frontend-engineer` — frontend code (only if applicable)
- `ai-engineer` — RAG, prompts, model adapters, evals (only if applicable)
- `devops-engineer` — Docker, CI, IaC, observability
- `qa-engineer` — test strategy, fixtures, adversarial cases
- `domain-expert` — domain knowledge, rule mapping, citations
- `technical-writer` — docs, runbooks, demo scripts
- `product-owner-reviewer` — end-of-phase business/risk review

## Slash commands

In `.claude/commands/`:

- `/start-session` — always run first thing in a session
- `/plan-feature <name>` — spec a feature with PM + architect (+ security/domain if relevant)
- `/build-feature <slug>` — implement an approved spec, vertical slice, TDD
- `/review-security [branch|path]` — security review on the diff
- `/run-qa [feature|phase]` — automated tests + qa-engineer review
- `/prepare-release [staging|prod]` — pre-deploy checklist
- `/phase-review N` — end-of-phase sign-off
- `/start-phase-team [N]` — launch parallel agent team (v2.1.32+; bounded to early phases)
- `/build-phase-autopilot [slugs|all]` — single-session chained autopilot (bounded scope)

